          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Is ambush marketing legal?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Usually yes, when done carefully. Directly infringing on trademarks (the Olympic rings, official logos, event names) is illegal. Clever campaigns that reference the moment without using protected marks generally fall within legal bounds — although event organisers push aggressive anti-ambush laws in host cities.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">Ambush marketing vs guerrilla marketing — what is the difference?</span>
